Advanced Git:

Foreword: We'll be discussing advanced concepts here.
This is not a beginner tutorial. If you know Git already, -> insightful.
If you dont -> you'll leave confused.

Git is a distributed SCM. Each repository contains the entire history of the project.

A commit is a snapshot in time of your entire project.

Git commits are inherently tied to one or more parent commits
Git commits are immutable

Back to Basics: The Commit

Traditional VCSs store history as a series of diffs. Git diff -> snapshot.

